HEADWORD: Manicate
<hw>Man"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>manicatus</ets> sleeved, fr. <ets>manica</ets> a sleeve.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with hairs or pubescence so platted
together and interwoven as to form a mass easily removed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

